        yuyutsum samupasthitaṁ<br /> [28]<br />

        sīdanti mama gātraṇi<br />
        mukhaṁ ca pariśuṣyati<br />
        vepathuśca ca śarīre me<br />
        romaharṣaśca jāyate<br /> [29]<br />
        gāṇḍīvaṁ sraṁsate<br />
        hastāttvakcaiva paridahyate<br />
        na ca śaknomyavasthātuṁ<br />
        bhramatīva c me manaḥ <br />[30]<br />
    </div>
    <p class="slokadescription">
        Seeing the close relatives arrayed in the battle field, to fight against his army, Arjuna was filled with compassion and told the following words to Krisna, in utter distress.
        My body becomes unsteady to stand straight, mouth is parching, and shiver runs all over the body and hair stand straight. (The divine bow Gandiva slips from the hand of Arjuna). He tells my body suffers from much heat, insufferable.
    </p>
    <hr class="slokadividerR" />
    <br />
    <div class="slokaDiv">
